resources.string: Praise, O praise our God and King;
My Shepherd, you supply my need,
How sweet the Name of Jesus sounds
Take the name of Jesus with you,
Lord, you left your throne
Who is He in yonder stall
There is no name so sweet on earth,
Tell me the old, old story,
Beneath the cross of Jesus
Jesus, keep me near the cross,
Low in the grave he lay, Jesus my Savior,
Holy, holy, holy! Lord God Almighty!
I hear Thy welcome voice
"Yet there is room:" the Lamb\'s bright hall of song,
Lord, I hear of showers of blessing,
Sinners Jesus will receive:
In loving-kindness Jesus came
Come to the Savior, make no delay -
There is a fountain filled with blood
Arise, my soul, arise,
The great Physician now is near,
Just as I am, without one plea,
O happy day that fixed my choice
I am so glad that our Father in heavâ€™n
Blessed assurance, Jesus is mine;
My Jesus, I love thee, I know thou art mine;
Jesus, lover of my soul,
Fight the good fight With all thy might;
1 I need thee every hour,
When storms around are sweeping,
Rock of Ages, cleft for me,
Peace, perfect peace, in this dark world of sin?
When we walk with the Lord
What a friend we have in Jesus,
Behold the servant of the Lord!
Jesus bids us shine
A few more years shall roll,
Jerusalem, my happy home,
Revive Thy work, O Lord,
Onward, Christian soldiers,
Stand up! stand up for Jesus!
Away in a manger, no crib for his bed,
Abide with me! fast falls the eventide;
